---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '')}/`;
const layers = [
  ['01', 'Direction', 'Active Cognition Computing', 'A framework for software that maintains useful, inspectable context around human intention.', 'research/acc/'],
  ['02', 'Network research', 'H-BFT', 'A conceptual protocol for human-bounded node authority, zero-knowledge authentication, and client-encrypted storage.', 'research/h-bft/'],
  ['03', 'Reasoning layer', 'PIL', 'A filesystem-based reasoning build system that derives state and runs specialized analysis passes over it.', 'projects/pil/'],
  ['04', 'Exploration layer', 'Explorer Engine', 'A deterministic engine that separates structured queries, result sets, and interchangeable renderers.', 'projects/explorer-engine/'],
  ['05', 'Workspace layer', 'Digital Center', 'A local-first capture-and-return workspace with shared references, Context Spaces, and explicit AI context.', 'projects/digital-center/'],
  ['06', 'Developer product', 'Semantic Workspace', 'Repository-native semantic metadata, saved views, and structured context bundles for developers and coding agents.', 'commercial/semantic-workspace/'],
];
---
<BaseLayout title="ACC Ecosystem Overview — Vivek Pragada" description="An overview of Active Cognition Computing and the systems that make up its research ecosystem.">
  <article class="shell py-14 sm:py-20">
    <header class="max-w-2xl border-b border-line pb-12">
      <p class="eyebrow">Overview</p>
      <h1 class="mt-5 text-4xl font-medium tracking-[-.035em] sm:text-5xl">Active Cognition Computing as a systems direction</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-base leading-8 text-muted">ACC begins with a simple observation: software stores artifacts well, but it rarely preserves the context that makes those artifacts meaningful. The ecosystem is a set of connected attempts to address that gap from theory through infrastructure and interface design.</p>
    </header>
    <section class="py-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">Primary direction</h2>
      <div class="prose-doc mt-5"><p>ACC shifts the center of software architecture from static containers toward an active, inspectable model of goals, relationships, working state, and unresolved questions. It is not a proposal for autonomous software. The aim is to make continuity easier while keeping inference subordinate to user intent.</p><p>The practical constraints are as important as the theory: context should remain understandable, core workflows should be local-first, and personal cognitive state should not depend on infrastructure the user cannot control.</p></div>
    </section>
    <section class="border-t border-line py-12">
      <p class="eyebrow">System map</p>
      <div class="mt-7">
        {layers.map(([n, layer, title, description, href]) => (
          <a href={`${base}${href}`} class="group grid gap-3 border-t border-line py-6 no-underline sm:grid-cols-[38px_105px_170px_1fr_auto]">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-dim">{n}</span><span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider text-signal">{layer}</span><strong class="text-sm font-medium text-ink">{title}</strong><span class="text-sm leading-6 text-muted">{description}</span><span class="text-signal">→</span>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="border-t border-line pt-12"><h2 class="text-2xl font-medium">How the components connect</h2><div class="prose-doc mt-5"><p>The framework defines the broader direction. Digital Center is the primary workspace where context, references, time, and active execution meet. PIL explores how raw personal information can be transformed into explicit derived state and layered reasoning outputs. Explorer Engine supplies a generic way to query structured collections and render the same results through different views.</p><p>H-BFT is the more speculative infrastructure branch, asking how identity, routing, storage, and recovery might work when sensitive state must remain sovereign. Semantic Workspace applies semantic organization to codebases, while the AI Systems Institute applies systems thinking to technical education through drills and connected artifacts.</p></div></section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
